HEADWORD: Calamander wood
<hw>Cal"a*man`der wood</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l"⟦adot⟧*m⟦acr⟧n`d⟦etil⟧r
w⟦oocr⟧d`)</pr>. <def>A valuable furniture wood from India and Ceylon,
of a hazel-brown color, with black stripes, very hard in texture. It is
a species of ebony, and is obtained from the <spn>Diospyros
qu⟦ae⟧sita</spn>. Called also <altname>Coromandel
wood</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

